  "content:encoded": "<p>This episode&#8217;s guest is WO2 Stan Egerton who served with the Toronto Scottish Regiment during World War 2.  Stan is the Toronto Scottish Regiment&#8217;s version of Saving Private Ryan because he was eager to serve with his two brothers; George and Frank.</p>\n<p>Stan lost his brothers in the second world war, and yet he speaks about them like he saw them only last week.  Another version of Stan&#8217;s story can be found at <a title=\"Interview with Stan Egerton\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/16645596\" target=\"_blank\">Vimeo.</a></p>\n<p>Please also check out a friend of the Canadian Military History Podcast at <a title=\"Afghanistan: A Soldier's Story\" href=\"http://www.afghanistanacanadianstory.ca/\" rel=\"home\">Afghanistan: A Soldier&#8217;s Story</a>.</p>\n<p>You can support this site by shopping on <a title=\"Amazon.ca\" href=\"http://www.amazon.ca?_encoding=UTF8&tag=thecanamilihi-20\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>.  You still enjoy <a title=\"Amazon.ca\" href=\"http://www.amazon.ca?_encoding=UTF8&tag=thecanamilihi-20\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>&#8216;s great prices, but a portion of your purchase goes to supporting the show.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-188-63\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Episode-007-WO2-Stan-Egerton-Part-1.mp3?_=63\" /><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Episode-007-WO2-Stan-Egerton-Part-1.mp3\">http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Episode-007-WO2-Stan-Egerton-Part-1.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-190\" alt=\"Stan\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan-300x168.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"168\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan-300x168.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan.jpg 960w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Stan sharing his memories with school children.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/HMCS-ASSINIBOINE-234.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-191\" alt=\"HMCS ASSINIBOINE 234\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/HMCS-ASSINIBOINE-234-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/HMCS-ASSINIBOINE-234-300x199.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/HMCS-ASSINIBOINE-234.jpg 470w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The ship that carried Stan to the beaches in Europe</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan2.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-192\" alt=\"Stan2\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan2-174x300.png\" width=\"174\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan2-174x300.png 174w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan2.png 383w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 174px) 100vw, 174px\" /></a> <a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan-Brothers.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-193\" alt=\"Stan Brothers\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan-Brothers-300x203.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"203\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan-Brothers-300x203.png 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Stan-Brothers.png 730w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Logo1400x1400.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-120\" alt=\"CMHP Logo1400x1400\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Logo1400x1400-300x300.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Logo1400x1400-300x300.png 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Logo1400x1400-150x150.png 150w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Logo1400x1400-1024x1024.png 1024w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/CMHP-Logo1400x1400.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n",
